        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 8:46AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 845 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lindsay, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lindsay, Alex, Bradley, Criner, Erin Springs, and Payne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
